               <p>467. 
               
                  <persName id="t17950916-97-defend999" type="defendantName">
                     RICHARD 
                     DOWELL
                  <interp inst="t17950916-97-defend999" type="surname" value="DOWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-defend999" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-defend999" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-defend999" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17950916-97-off553" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-off553" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-off553" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               feloniously stealing, on the <rs id="t17950916-97-cd554" type="crimeDate">1st of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-97-off553 t17950916-97-cd554"></join>, a woman's linen apron, value 2s.
            </rs> the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17950916-97-victim1001" type="victimName">
                     Mary 
                     Allen
                  <interp inst="t17950916-97-victim1001" type="surname" value="Allen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-victim1001" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-victim1001" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-97-off553 t17950916-97-victim1001"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            , <rs id="t17950916-97-viclabel555" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17950916-97-victim1001 t17950916-97-viclabel555"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17950916-97-person1002">
                  GEORGE
                   ALLEN
               <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1002" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1002" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1002" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>Q. Have you a sister? - Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. What is her name? - Mary.</p>
               <p>Q. A single woman? - Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Did she lose any property at any time? - Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you keep house together? - No. I am a cook.</p>
               <p>Q. Had you the care of the linen apron that was stole? - Yes, I had. On the 1st of August I was standing with several other people, to see a horse that had fell<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179509160253"></xptr>down; a witness, Slark, came up to me and told me that I had my pocket picked; I felt and I missed my apron that I had in my pocket before, a linen apron; I brought it from a relation's where my sister had left it; I was going to her; I was bringing it from Maiden-lane, Wood-street to Westminster. Slark told me that was the person, pointing to the prisoner; he had then ran across the way; both of us pursued him, and we took him in Bridge-street.</p>

               <p>Q. Did you lose sight of him? - No. A constable was close by, and several people see us stop, and a constable, to see what was the matter, and I gave charge of him to the constable. I found the apron under his great coat.</p>
               <p>Q. Who has kept the apron ever since? - The constable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17950916-97-person1003">
                  THOMAS
                   SLARK
               <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1003" type="surname" value="SLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1003" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1003" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a glass cutter; I see the prisoner, pick Allen's pocket and put it under his coat, and I told Allen of it, and pursued him and took him myself.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you see what he had taken? - I had not.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you know Mr. Allen at that time? - I did not, he was a stranger to me.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you ever lose sight of him? - No.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you find the apron on him? - Yes, under his coat.</p>
               <p>Q. To whom was it delivered? - To the constable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17950916-97-person1004">
                  JOSHUA
                   GRAY
               <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1004" type="surname" value="GRAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1004" type="given" value="JOSHUA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1004" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a constable; I was coming along Bridge-street, and I see two men got hold of the prisoner at the bar by the collar, and I came up, and they said he had picked a pocket of this apron; so I took him into custody, and took the property at the same time. I see it taken from him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He did not see it taken from me.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. This is the apron, I know it by the mark 
               <persName id="t17950916-97-person1005">
                  M.
                   A. 
               <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1005" type="surname" value="A."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1005" type="given" value="M."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-person1005" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            2.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you know that mark on it before you lost it? - I did.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I left off work about three o'clock on Saturday afternoon, I was going over the water to Kent-street; I am a sawyer by trade; going by Fleet-market, there was a horse fell down in a cart, and this apron fell down from somebody, and I picked it up, and was going on, and these men came and stopped me with it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called two witnesses who gave him a very good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17950916-97-verdict556" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17950916-97-verdict556" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. (Aged 21.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17950916-97-punish557" type="punishmentDescription">
